00:06:46.200 --> 00:06:50.160
NARRATOR:
Year after year, the Miss
America Pageant would struggle

00:06:50.160 --> 00:06:52.860
to pull off
a delicate balancing act:

00:06:52.860 --> 00:06:55.000
Objectifying women

00:06:55.000 --> 00:06:58.030
while providing them
with real opportunities;

00:06:58.030 --> 00:07:00.160
promoting traditional roles

00:07:00.160 --> 00:07:02.630
while encouraging
women's independence;

00:07:02.630 --> 00:07:05.360
glorifying feminine modesty

00:07:05.360 --> 00:07:08.760
while trading
on female sexuality.

00:07:08.760 --> 00:07:12.130
Along the way,
it would come to be a barometer

00:07:12.130 --> 00:07:16.300
of the nation's shifting ideas
about American womanhood.

00:07:18.800 --> 00:07:20.760
But in 1921,

00:07:20.760 --> 00:07:24.660
Atlantic City's businessmen were
simply trying to turn a profit

00:07:24.660 --> 00:07:30.730
by capitalizing on the country's
fascination with beauty.

