00:29:57.400 --> 00:30:01.160
that I'm the daughter
of Louie and Bella Myerson."

00:30:01.160 --> 00:30:06.500
NARRATOR:
On September 3, Myerson and
the other contestants appeared

00:30:06.500 --> 00:30:07.900
on Atlantic City's Boardwalk

00:30:07.900 --> 00:30:10.930
for the Miss America Pageant's
opening ceremony:

00:30:10.930 --> 00:30:15.300
a victory parade to celebrate
the end of the war.

00:30:15.300 --> 00:30:19.100
In the crowd was Myerson's
older sister Sylvia.

00:30:19.100 --> 00:30:21.630
Her mother,
who spoke no English,

00:30:21.630 --> 00:30:24.160
had been left at home
in the Bronx.

00:30:26.160 --> 00:30:31.460
MYERSON:
The first night, I compete
with a group of girls on talent.

00:30:31.460 --> 00:30:33.000
I won.

00:30:33.000 --> 00:30:36.700
Headline says,
"Jewish Girl in Atlantic City

00:30:36.700 --> 00:30:40.530
