I owed it to those women
to give them a present, a gift.

00:31:37.060 --> 00:31:38.530
That, to them, was the gift.

00:31:40.400 --> 00:31:42.800
NARRATOR:
On the second night
of preliminaries,

00:31:42.800 --> 00:31:47.330
Myerson scored another win,
in the swimsuit competition,

00:31:47.330 --> 00:31:51.600
and she now seemed a strong
favorite for the finals.

00:31:51.600 --> 00:31:53.230
"The new Miss America
will either be

00:31:53.230 --> 00:31:55.530
Miss New York City,
Bess Myerson,"

00:31:55.530 --> 00:31:57.460
one newspaper predicted,

00:31:57.460 --> 00:31:59.500
"or somebody else."

00:32:01.230 --> 00:32:03.830
MALE ANNOUNCER:
They're about to pick
Miss America of 1945.

00:32:03.830 --> 00:32:06.800
FEMALE ANNOUNCER:
Well, they've made their choice,

00:32:06.800 --> 00:32:08.960
